by the surface tension of the water.<\/li>\n<li>The fully <em>isn't<\/em> porous to air when fully grown, but it <em>is<\/em> porous to air while it's still developing.<\/li>\n<li>The fruit does some amount of photosynthesis, and the air is waste oxygen.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n","question_id":7728,"tags":["fruit"],"score":11,"accepted_answer_id":7730,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":1059,"up_vote_count":11},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://graph.facebook.com/100000058307963/picture?type=large","user_type":"registered","user_id":3322,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3322/aram-alipoor","reputation":123,"display_name":"Aram Alipoor"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/aab80aeaf4754dee5d4a758db50e7213?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":460,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/460/memming","reputation":2145,"display_name":"Memming","accept_rate":70},"score":0,"post_id":7718,"edited":false,"creation_date":1364827668,"comment_id":9681,"body":"One side note: even with eyes &quot;closed&quot;, light penetrates your eye lids, and you can see things. Of course they are very very blurry."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/NjVUE.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3082,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3082/armacino","reputation":50,"display_name":"Armacino"},"score":0,"post_id":7718,"edited":false,"creation_date":1364848450,"comment_id":9692,"body":"Two weeks ago, I watched this video. <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qLziFMF4DHA&amp;list=UUTVCr29RCZJI0CIG2SJgPgA&amp;index=9\" rel=\"nofollow\">youtube.com/&hellip;<\/a> In here, how this guy sense the things around him is not clear (it says he uses echo location to navigate, but is it really true?). However it is an interesting documentary. I hope this will help you as a different example."}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6a43651dba3f306d9c